$ Office Object Model: Excel - Application.inputBox

`inputBox()` lets the user enter different values or → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range].


{ Entering basic types

  With the `type` → development/languages/VBA/language/subs-and-functions/parameters[parameter] set to 1, 2 or 4, `application.inputBox` allows to enter
  numbers, → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/string[strings] or → development/languages/VBA/language/datatypes/boolean[booleans].

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Application/inputBox/number-string-boolean.bas||

}
{ Entering ranges

  With `type := 8`, `inputBox` lets the user enter a → Microsoft/Office/Excel/Object-Model/Range[range] by selecting it with the mouse (and then process the range in the VBA code).

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Application/inputBox/range.bas||

  gh|about-MS-Office-object-model|/Excel/Application/inputBox/img/range.png||

}


sa:
  The VBA function → development/languages/VBA/functions/inputBox[`inputBox()`]
